    {
      "id": 20,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Alert Thresholds and Investigation Guide",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 16,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 78
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "# Aviation Weather Cache - Operations Guide\n\n## Critical Alerts\n\n### 🔴 CRITICAL: Pull Failure\n**Condition:** `Last Successful Pull Age > 600s` (10 minutes)\n\n**Impact:** Stale data being served, cache not updating\n\n**Investigation:**\n1. Check `Pull Error Rate` panel - are errors occurring?\n2. Verify network connectivity to aviationweather.gov\n3. Check service logs for HTTP errors or XML parse failures\n4. Verify aviationweather.gov is accessible: `curl -I https://aviationweather.gov/data/api/metar`\n\n**Resolution:**\n- Transient network issues: Wait for next pull cycle (default 5min)\n- Persistent errors: Check upstream service status\n- Parse errors: May indicate schema change, requires code update\n\n---\n\n### 🟡 WARNING: Stale Data\n**Condition:** `Data Freshness Percentage < 80%`\n\n**Impact:** Most stations serving old METARs\n\n**Investigation:**\n1. Check `METAR Age Distribution` - is upstream data stale?\n2. Review `Oldest METAR Age` - are specific stations never updating?\n3. This may be normal for rarely-reporting stations\n\n**Resolution:**\n- If upstream issue: Nothing to do, cache merging preserves data\n- If cache issue: Investigate pull logic\n\n---\n\n### 🟡 WARNING: High Query Latency\n**Condition:** `Average Query Latency > 100ms` OR `p99 Latency > 500ms`\n\n**Impact:** Slow API responses, poor user experience\n\n**Investigation:**\n1. Check `Query Rate` - is load unusually high?\n2. Review `Query Traffic Analysis` - is a single station being hammered?\n3. Check CPU/memory usage of service\n\n**Resolution:**\n- High load: Consider rate limiting or caching at reverse proxy\n- Slow queries: Profile field filtering logic\n\n---\n\n## Warning Conditions\n\n### 🟠 Low Station Count\n**Condition:** `Total Stations < 2000`\n\n**Likely Cause:** Pull failures, incomplete data from upstream\n\n**Action:** Check pull metrics and logs\n\n---\n\n### 🟠 High Cache Miss Rate\n**Condition:** Sustained spikes in `Stations Not in Cache`\n\n**Likely Cause:** Invalid station IDs, typos in queries, or missing upstream data\n\n**Action:** Review top missing stations - are they valid ICAO codes?\n\n---\n\n## Key Metrics Summary\n\n| Metric | Healthy Range | Warning | Critical |\n|--------|--------------|---------|----------|\n| Pull Age | < 300s | 300-600s | > 600s |\n| Pull Errors (1h) | 0 | 1-2 | > 2 |\n| Data Freshness | > 80% | 60-80% | < 60% |\n| Query Latency (avg) | < 100ms | 100-500ms | > 500ms |\n| Total Stations | > 2000 | 1000-2000 | < 1000 |\n\n---\n\n## Normal Behavior Notes\n\n- **Cache never purges:** Old data remains until replaced. This is by design.\n- **Age metrics update every 10s:** Pull age increases linearly between pulls.\n- **Pull interval is 5 minutes by default:** Configured via `update_interval` in config.\n- **Silent omissions are normal:** Stations filtered by age or not cached don't error, just omitted from results.\n- **Oldest METAR can be very old:** Some stations report infrequently or are inactive.\n\n---\n\n## Useful Prometheus Queries\n\n```promql\n# Alert on pull failure\navweather_last_successful_pull_age_seconds > 600\n\n# Alert on high error rate\nrate(avweather_pull_errors_total[5m]) > 0.01\n\n# Alert on low freshness\n(avweather_stations_under_1hour / avweather_total_stations) < 0.6\n\n# Alert on high latency\nhistogram_quantile(0.99, rate(avweather_query_latency_seconds_bucket[5m])) > 0.5\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dashboard Time Ranges\n\n- **Real-time Monitoring:** 1 hour (default)\n- **Incident Investigation:** 6-24 hours\n- **Trend Analysis:** 7-30 days\n- **Performance Baseline:** 90 days\n\n---\n\n## Related Resources\n\n- Service Logs: Check container/pod logs for detailed error messages\n- Prometheus: Full metric listing at `/metrics` endpoint\n- Source Data: https://aviationweather.gov/data/api/metar\n- Repository: Check CLAUDE.md for architecture details\n"
      }
